title: 30 SIMPLE KITCHEN HACKS YOU'D WISH YOU'D KNOWN SOONER
tags: 5-Minute Crafts,DIY,Do it yourself,crafts,trucos,5 minutes craft,life hacks,5 minute craft,trucos de belliza,proyectos faciles,useful things,lifehacks,tricks,tips,DIY projects,DIY activities,Handcraft,Tutorial,howto,handmade,homemade,make,create,juicer,cook,bake,bake bacon,orange fresh,orange juice,metal cooling rack,baking sheet,foil,cooking spray,paper towels,bacon grease
description: SIMPLE KITCHEN HACKSMaking perfect bacon is easier than you might think. I used to forgo making bacon because the gigantic mess it made just wasn’t worth the amazing taste. A few years ago I learned about baking bacon and it has changed my life forever!Why should you bake your bacon?Baked bacon does not curl – you get nice straight bacon pieces every time.Cooks evenly – no white fatty pieces on one end and burnt bacon on the other.No splattering of bacon grease all over the place.No need to babysit the bacon. You don’t even have to turn it over!Tastes delicious!What you will need to bake bacon:Shallow baking sheetFoil (heavy-duty preferable)Metal cooling rack (optional)Non-stick cooking spray (optional)Paper towels- Line the  baking sheet with foil. (You will want to use a baking sheet that has enough of a rim that it contains the bacon drippings.)- If using a metal cooling rack, spray the rack with non-stick cooking spray, and place the rack inside the baking sheet.- Place the bacon slices in a single layer either directly on the foil or on a rack. Make sure not to overlap slices.- Turn the oven on and set to 400 degrees. Do not wait for the oven to preheat. Go ahead and place the pan in the oven.- Cook the bacon for 12-17 minutes. Cooking time depends on the thickness of your bacon, and how long it takes for your oven to come to temperature. Start checking your bacon around 10 minutes to ensure your bacon doesn’t burn. (Nothing worse than burnt bacon!)- When the bacon is golden brown, the bacon is done.- Once the bacon has reached your desired level of crispiness, remove immediately and place on paper towels to soak up the bacon grease.Another great idea! I hate squeezing oranges but I love fresh squeezed orange juice. So, if you don’t have a juicer, this one costs you nothing but a couple of soda or water bottles!You’ll just have to try this to see how easy and convenient it is! I couldn’t wait to see how it worked, so I tried it right away and it works like a charm! My kids were so fascinated that you could do this. As a result, I’m buying a lot more oranges!  : )TIMESTAMPS:0:36 Let's bake some bacon!2:23 How to store an apple4:36 Cookie decor idea9:42 Sausage star breakfast14:08 Awesome juicer----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Our Social Media:Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/5min.crafts/Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/5.min.crafts/Twitter: https://twitter.com/5m_craftsSubscribe to 5-Minute MAGIC: http://bit.ly/2ldditZSubscribe to 5-Minute Crafts GIRLY: https://goo.gl/fWbJqzSubscribe 5-Minute Crafts KIDS: https://goo.gl/PEuLVtThe Bright Side of Youtube: https://goo.gl/rQTJZz----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------For more videos and articles visit:http://www.brightside.meMusic by Epidemic Sound: https://www.epidemicsound.com/

A little tricky as sugar syrup is involved in this. But it is worth a try as these tastes just awesome. Do try this time consuming yet delicious recipe this Diwali and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:• 2 cups Besan• About 1 1/4 cup Water• Oil for frying• 2 cups Sugar• 1 cup Water• 1 tbsp Raisins• 1 tbsp chopped Cashew nuts• 1 tbsp sliced Almonds• 1/4 tsp Cardamom powderMethod:• In a bowl take besan. • Add a little water at a time and mix it well. • Do not add all the water at a time or lumps of besan will be   formed. • Try to use beater for mixing that will help to break the lumps. • The consistency of batter should be like pakoda batter, neither   too thick nor too thin. • Mix the batter well continuously with the beater for about 4-5   minutes. • The batter should be nice, smooth and light. • Rest the batter for about 10-15 minutes. • In a pan take sugar and add water in it. • Turn on the gas on medium heat and let the sugar dissolve   completely. • Cook the syrup for 5 minutes more on medium heat after sugar   has melted completely. • The syrup should have 2 thread consistency. • It should be nice, thick and not free flowing. • Turn off the gas and sugar syrup is already. • Heat up oil on medium heat. • Stir the batter well and spread it in the bundi making zara that is   held on the pan. • Tap the zara to make nice round bundi. • If you don’t have bundi making zara then you can use regular zara  that is used for frying or a grater. • Make sure to use small shrade grater. • After every use of regular zara or grater wipe the lower side to   remove the batter stuck there. • Stir the batter well before making each batch of bundi. • Fry bundi on medium heat. • Take the fried bundi out into a strainer to drain excess oil if any. • Boil the sugar syrup once more and add fried bundi, raisins,   cashew nuts, almonds, cardamom powder. • Mix everything well together and let the mixture rest for an hour. • After an hour roll the ladoos. • Take the mixture in hand and roll ladoos pressing the bundi   together.• Bundiche ladoo are already.Subscribe to my other title: കുക്കറിൽ വെച്ച് രുചികരമായ റവ കേക്ക് || No Egg No Butter No OVEN  Rava Cake | Cake in Pressure Cooker
tags: [none]
description: Ingredients:Rava / Sooji / Semolina – 1 cup (Unroasted)Maida / All purpose flour - ½ cupThick curd (Not sour) – ½ cupSugar – ½ cup (Powdered)Oil – ½ cup (I used sunflower oil)Vanilla essence – 1 tspMilk – 3 tbsp (Or coconut milk)Baking powder - ½ tspBaking soda – ¼ tspSteps:Mix oil, sugar and curd.Add baking soda, baking powder and vanilla essence and mix well.Add maida in batches and mix well.Add rava and mix well.Add milk and mix well.Add more milk, if the mixture becomes too thick.Grease a 6-inch baking pan with butter.Line it with butter paper / parchment baking paper.Mix the batter well and transfer to the pan. (The batter should not be more than three fourth of the pan)Level it with a spatula. Gently tap the pan to get rid of air bubbles.To bake the cake, heat a pressure cooker with 2 cups of salt. You can reuse this salt for 2-3 times.Level the salt by gently shaking the cooker.Place an inverted steel plate as a base on the salt.Cover without the whistle and heat up the salt on high heat for 3-4 minutes.Place the baking pan on to the base and cook covered without the whistle on a medium flame (on the large burner).Bake for 45 minutes on medium heat and for 7 minutes on low heat or until the toothpick inserted at the center comes out clean.Transfer the pan from cooker and allow it to cool.Run a knife through the edges and unmould once it cools down.Remove the butter paper.Enjoy the rava cake!Rava Cake in oven - http://y2u.be/GSvsdyyd9yQRava Cake in Pressure Cooker without maida - http://y2u.be/4Kp4fNi61LAMarble Cake in Pressure Cooker - http://y2u.be/R5DCPNltlRgLemon Cake in Pressure Cooker - http://y2u.be/e8IITseBhloBanana Cake in Pressure Cooker - http://y2u.be/sQxNMEFsKjsChocolate Cake in Pressure Cooker - http://y2u.be/BJwdrFHEDBkMia Kitchen Beginner's cooking channel - https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvrKA2V99QpgpeS7UPIPA_QFollow me on Facebook -https://www.facebook.com/MiaasKitchen/Twitter - https://twitter.com/KitchenMiaMail me - miakitchen2014@gmail.comiOS App - https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mia-kitchen/id1348204794Android App - https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=xyz.appmaker.miakitchen

description: 2019 से पहले 1992 आ रहा है बल्कि आ चुका है. इंतज़ार अब इस बात का है कि प्रधानमंत्री नरेंद्र मोदी कब 1992 के इस सियासी खेल में उतरते हैं. 2014 में प्रधानमंत्री की उम्मीदवार के तौर पर नरेंद्र मोदी के भाषणों को याद कीजिए, क्या आपको कोई भाषण याद आता है, जो मुख्य रूप से राम मंदिर पर केंद्रित हो. उस चुनाव में मां गंगा ज़रूर आ गई थीं मगर राम मंदिर का सवाल मेनिफिस्टो में किसी किनारे दर्ज था. 2014 के मेनिफेस्टों में राम मंदिर का ज़िक्र पेज नंबर 37 पर था. 38 पेज के मेनिफेस्टों में 37वें पेज पर वो भी तीन लाइन. मगर कुछ दिनों से राम मंदिर बीजेपी और संघ के नेताओं के भाषण में पहले पन्ने पर आ गया है. सवाल है प्रधानमंत्री मोदी कब राम मंदिर पर भाषण देंगे.NDTV is one of the leaders in the production and broadcasting of un-biased and comprehensive news and entertainment programmes in India and abroad. description: On today's show, Ravish Kumar asks why the RBI isn't disclosing the names of loan defaulters who have led to NPA crisis in India's banking system. While farmers commit suicide due to harassment by banks to repay the agricultural loans taken by them, are 'VIP' loan defaulters being given a free run? Central Information Commission has issued a show cause notice to RBI governor for not disclosing the wilful defaulters list. Central Information Commissioner (CIC) M Sridhar Acharyulu says that the Supreme Court had already rejected all the objections raised by RBI on the matter of disclosing names of defaulters and that the RBI is failing to comply with the court's order.
